        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-08-14 10:13:48.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(6 comments)\n\nThe reason for these copyTo methods was to allow seamless reading from and writing to the database. The way the DAO/JPA works (or worked a few years ago when I worked on this) means that it does not actually read everything from the database, it does a cached read where it only copies the top object of a hierarchy. It's only if you descend the object hierarchy that additional reads are done to read contained objects. The idea of the copyTo() method was to force a traversal of the entire object hierarchy tree and force a full copy of all the objects.\n\nThis code was originally designed to work towards Postgres and MariaDB may work differently.\n\nWe need to be sure that his behaviour is preserved.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
